results.name: Number of distinct GCDs of nonempty submultisets of the integer partition with Heinz number n.
comment: The Heinz number of an integer partition (y_1,...,y_k) is prime(y_1)*...*prime(y_k).
Number of distinct values obtained when A289508 is applied to all divisors of n larger than one. - _Antti Karttunen_, Sep 28 2018
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
example: 455 is the Heinz number of (6,4,3) which has possible GCDs of nonempty submultisets {1,2,3,4,6} so a(455) = 5.
program: A316555(n) = { my(m=Map(),s,k=0); fordiv(n,d,if((d>1)&&!mapisdefined(m,s=A289508(d)), mapput(m,s,s); k++)); (k); }; \\ _Antti Karttunen_, Sep 28 2018
xref: Cf. also A304793, A305611, A319685, A319695 for other similarly constructed sequences.
